TRAN TRUNG DUNG is a Junior AI/ML Engineer with 0.33 years of commercial experience. Their core expertise lies in developing Classification Models, Regression Models, Clustering Models, and Transformer Models using Scikit-learn, TensorFlow, PyTorch, and HuggingFace, with a strong foundation in techniques such as Algorithms, Machine Learning, Data Processing, Natural Language Processing, Data Modeling, and Model Performance Evaluation. As an AI R&D Research Engineer Intern at WISDOM Engineering & Business Solutions, they contributed to research and prototyping of AI models for business and engineering solutions, preprocessing datasets, applying NLP and ML algorithms, and evaluating model performance, with a notable 4-month duration of collaboration with senior engineers on experimentation, testing, and reporting of AI-driven approaches.

Technically, they are proficient in Python and SQL, and have hands-on experience with tools such as Git, Jupyter Notebook, and Colab, as well as libraries like Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, and Seaborn. Their experience spans both commercial and academic projects, including the development of NLP models using HuggingFace Transformers, where they fine-tuned multilingual models and designed data preprocessing pipelines, and university coursework projects, where they implemented ML models and built database-driven applications with SQL and data visualization in Python. With a strong educational background in Computer Science from Ton Duc Thang University HCMC, they possess a solid understanding of data structures, probability, linear algebra, and optimization, making them a well-rounded junior engineer with a promising career ahead in the field of AI and ML.